cs.NE, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CV, cs.SY

The paper is about developing a randomized approach for building deep neural networks, which falls under the category of neural networks (cs.NE). The paper also establishes a fundamental result on the universal approximation property, which is a topic in machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper presents a learning algorithm for implementing the proposed model, which involves evaluating read-out weights, a technique commonly used in computer vision (cs.CV) and control systems (cs.SY). Therefore, the most likely categories are cs.NE, cs.LG, and cs.AI, followed by cs.CV and cs.SY.
